# Copy to .env.database.remote (gitignored). Used by pnpm db:prisma:push:remote
#
# Pooled (transaction mode) — good for serverless / many short connections. Use ?pgbouncer=true with Prisma.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.YOUR_REF:YOUR_PASSWORD@aws-1-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true
#
# Session pooler :5432 — used by Prisma CLI for migrate / db push (see prisma.config.ts migrate.url + directUrl).
DIRECT_URL=postgresql://postgres.YOUR_REF:YOUR_PASSWORD@aws-1-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres
#
# After migrations are on this database, seed demo logins + content into THIS remote DB:
#   admin@hanover.test / user@hanover.test — password HanoverTest123!
#   (written to auth.users + auth.identities + public.users, then demo content rows)
# From repo root:
#   pnpm db:prisma:seed:remote
